00:06.502 --> 00:10.526
as he came around one time. He kicked me on the leg. I 
was incapacitated for three months with that one

00:13.990 --> 00:20.177
call. That really ensured my not calling him 
anymore. But it is one of those things that happens

00:25.062 --> 00:30.628
to you. Now, did you, within small animal, you're 
still doing a general practice. Is there any kind

00:37.320 --> 00:42.805
of, you didn't specialize in any facet or anything 
like that? Small animals, yes. I tried to take

00:45.228 --> 00:59.181
extra courses and continue the education in 
ophthalmology and surgery.

01:04.443 --> 01:13.716
And dermatology, particularly

01:04.443 --> 01:13.716
dermatology.

01:13.756 --> 01:18.342
I was a member of all those associations at one time 
to the National Association. Did you begin any

01:18.362 --> 01:22.327
kind of referral practice along the way 
somewhere? Yes, we had referrals from

01:22.808 --> 01:29.337
surrounding towns, particularly for surgery. 
Oh, okay. So they're coming to you for the surgery

01:30.716 --> 01:33.379
and dermatology? Yes. How about you now? Are you 
referring any of your patients to a specialist?

01:37.744 --> 01:38.024
Oh, yes. We refer lots to Dallas. They set up a 
referral clinic over there that had a very good

01:40.767 --> 01:53.262
surgeon, a board man, a board radiologist, and a 
board dermatologist. Who is it? Reedy was a

01:54.503 --> 01:55.865
dermatologist. Reedy? Okay. He'll be in this 
afternoon. Oh, I'll see him tomorrow, rather.

02:00.628 --> 02:01.048
That's right. I'll see Reggie tomorrow. What's 
his name? Gosh, he's in here. He was a surgeon. He's

02:09.237 --> 02:10.779
retired now. And the radiologist is still there. 
She's taking a partner. She's a ladybird. And they

02:19.909 --> 02:26.897
were very running in a high quality type thing. 
They never tried to give shots and do things like

02:28.793 --> 02:32.899
that. Of course, I was minoring in dermatology, 
but Reedy was a board man and taught some with the

02:33.099 --> 02:47.340
medical school over there. Because that's the 
conversion of the profession. We were very slow at

02:51.726 --> 02:56.293
it and very jealous.

02:57.067 --> 02:59.430
They have not accepted it until recent years. In my 
time, it was not done hardly at all. Do you see that

03:04.576 --> 03:08.861
as sort of the coming trend in veterinary 
practice? Oh, yeah. Specialization and referral

03:09.582 --> 03:11.425
practices? Quite a lot, yeah. A general 
practitioner who basically does the client

03:13.107 --> 03:20.796
ministry and then refers the more critical 
problems? Yeah, Herman Dietrich was a surgeon.

03:22.779 --> 03:25.622
Herman Dietrich, in fact, I think I may have met him 
at the... He might have sat at the table with me. He

03:31.219 --> 03:34.383
lives in Dallas and Colorado.

03:37.287 --> 03:47.239
D-I-E-T-R-I-C-H.

